td.p:
The present request for a preliminary ruling concerns the interpretation of Directive 2011/7/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 February 2011 on combating late payment in commercial transactions (
OJ 2011 L 48, p. 1
).

A number of substantive changes are to be made to Directive 2000/35/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 29 June 2000 on combating late payment in commercial transactions [
OJ 2000 L 200, p. 35
]. It is desirable, for reasons of clarity and rationalisation, that the provisions in question should be recast.
